<br>
PoH was a different zone than it is now when it was put on the calendar.  If it is going to remain on the calendar in its new form, I should hope that RTA has a better justification than the simple convenience of the member guild who reserves the zone getting the entire zone to itself.  <br>
<br>
In particular, the NE corner zone is good for xp grinding in the mid 50's.  It's nowhere near Maestro and Inny.  Why shouldn't a group ro groups be able to do their thing there while a guild who's reserved the only tenably reservable mobs in the zone--Inny and Maestro--does its thing on the other end of the zone? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saediien>Saediien</A> at: 8/12/03 2:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1908<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/12/03 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of Hate</span><hr size=1> PoH is on a Calendar, not a Rotation.  The only thing needed to be able to reserve it is 40 members to post.   There are no &quot;turns&quot;, except that you cannot have 2 reservations for the same Plane at the same time.<br>
<br>
IF your group(s) want to go up, and your guild is a Reserving Entity, just Reserve a date you want to go there.  Once you complete your date, you can immediately reserve another (except you can't reserve today for today).<br>
<br>
OR go there any day that's not reserved.<br>
<br>
OR have a 'majority' of Reserving Guilds agree that the Calendar for Hate is no longer needed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saediien>Saediien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/12/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of Hate</span><hr size=1> The whole point of this thread is to explore why the new Plane of Hate is still on the calendar (thanks for noting the calendar/rotation distiction, my mistake) for any reason other than inertia or self-interest.*<br>
<br>
I don't imagine the prospects for getting Hate off the calendar are at all good.   Why on earth would the guilds who already have the edge of being able to claim the zone for themselves give up that advantage?  Who wouldn't want to be able to reserve an entire zone for one's big bad self?  My point is that there is no justification for why they should be able to do so, other than &quot;because&quot;--the best justification I've seen offered so far.<br>
<br>
It is certainly in the self-interest of the guilds who want to reserve the entire zone to do so.  But why should they get that advantage, and how does that advantage benefit the residents and guilds of the Rathe as a whole?  Inny and Maestro could be put on rotation for the guilds that want to take him out.  I've still waiting for a good reason for the whole new zone to remain on the calendar.  Unfortunately, though, as you've laid out the situation Nyca, the Reserving Guilds need not justify their position to anyone other than themselves.  RTA has had the chance to &quot;check out&quot; the new Hate for three months now.  The Reserving Guilds should remember that holding on to the calendar status of the new Hate for what appear to be crassly self-motivated reasons undermines the legitimacy of RTA itself.<br>
<br>
*I know that I can go when the zone isn't reserved.  And I know there is a process I could undertake to be able to reserve the zone.  However, I don't understand why the new plane of hate is reservable in the first place--in fact I don't think it should be, so I'd be intellectually dishonest if I went about reserving the zone. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saediien>Saediien</A> at: 8/12/03 3:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1909<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/12/03 3:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane of Hate</span><hr size=1> Saediien said:<br>
