<br>
What is it that you think the old Plane of Hate was booked for?  Inny and Maestro alone?  That is what you are suggesting.  When Shadows of Yamabushi used to go to hate every couple of weekends we went up there to farm Pally, Warrior, Enchanter epic pieces, armor for less well equipped players, etc.  Not once did we kill Inny.  In fact...we didn't even ENGAGE (but once or twice to test our mettle) him because that's not what we were there for.  We were there to kill a zone full of mobs repeatedly to get semi-random drop epic items (yes, one of those items was related to Maestro, but that is beside the point now).  What is NOT beside the point though, is that smaller to mid range guilds wanting to complete epics for their members and outfit them in some low-end raiding gear STILL need to go to the Plane of Hate.<br>
<br>
Why should those guilds not benefit from being able to reserve the plane to farm for epics and armor?  and then when they are large enough and powerful enough, why should they not be able to have the zone to themselves to clear for additional drops (pally and enchanter), with the additional goal of attemping maestro for the first time.<br>
<br>
You seem to think that posting entities are being selfish by wanting to reserve a plane to hunt there alone.  Well...I think you are being selfish by not looking at the big picture, as well as ASSuming why a guild might want to book the plane in the first place.<br>
<br>
Do me a favor, take Nyca's list of guilds who reserve the Plane of Hate and tell me which ones can kill Maestro and Inny.  Then sit there and think about why they are *really* reserving the plane.  OMG, its for the same reason everyone has always reserved it.<br>
<br>
Case closed. <p><P><br>
